# Server Components, server actions, and Zod

## Data retrieval

- Load application data from the database (and pass it into the UI tree) in **React Server Components** only.
- Do not use Client Components or client-side `fetch` to internal routes as the primary way to read app data that belongs in the server-rendered tree.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — client component fetching app data for the page
"use client";
export function Page() {
  const [data, setData] = useState(null);
  useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/items").then(...); }, []);
}

// ✅ GOOD — async Server Component reads and passes props
export default async function Page() {
  const items = await db.select().from(itemsTable);
  return <List items={items} />;
}
```

## Inserts, updates, deletes

- All **database writes** (`insert`, `update`, `delete`) must run inside **`"use server"` server actions**. Do not call Drizzle/`db` from Client Components or use client `fetch` to internal mutation routes as the default pattern when a server action can carry the operation.

## Validation

- Validate all external and user-supplied input with **Zod** (`z.object`, etc.) before use in server actions or persistence.
- Server action arguments must be validated with a Zod schema and exposed as a **TypeScript type** (e.g. `z.infer<typeof mySchema>`). **Do not** type server action parameters as `FormData` (parse `FormData` inside the action if needed, then validate a plain object with Zod).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — FormData as the public contract
"use server";
export async function saveItem(formData: FormData) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — schema + inferred type; validate then mutate
import { z } from "zod";

const saveItemSchema = z.object({ title: z.string().min(1), id: z.string().uuid() });
export type SaveItemInput = z.infer<typeof saveItemSchema>;

"use server";
export async function saveItem(input: SaveItemInput) {
  const data = saveItemSchema.parse(input);
  await db.update(items).set({ title: data.title }).where(eq(items.id, data.id));
}
```

## Clerk

- Resolve identity on the server (e.g. `auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`) inside Server Components and server actions; combine with ownership checks per `clerk-auth-data-isolation.mdc`.
